# Cursor Rules — Agentra DingBot

You are working on a Python multi-agent crypto trading bot.

## Imports
All source is in `src/`. pytest.ini adds it to PYTHONPATH.
Import as: `from core.config import ...` (NOT `from src.core.config import ...`)

## TDD
Write failing tests BEFORE any implementation. No exceptions.

## Critical patterns
- LangGraph _wrap(): shallow dict ONLY (`{f.name: getattr(s, f.name) for f in fields(s)}`)
- errors field: Annotated[List[str], operator.add] — never return full accumulated list
- Routing: string keys "execute"/"skip" in add_conditional_edges
- Kill switch: check KillSwitch.is_armed() before every order
- Live gate: is_live_trading_enabled() must be True for any real order
- FreqTrade: HTTP calls only, never import the package (GPL boundary)

## Test file locations
tests/test_step6_backtest.py — backtesting validation
tests/test_step7_executor.py — executor safety
tests/test_langgraph_pipeline.py — integration tests
tests/test_ml_bridge.py — ML bridge
